<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T007 Cleanup Rescue Pack</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.45;color:#111827}h1{color:#0f172a}h2{border-bottom:1px solid #cbd5e1}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:12px 0}td,th{border:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding:8px}th{background:#e2e8f0}.note{background:#f8fafc;border-left:5px solid #64748b;padding:10px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Cleanup Rescue Pack</h1><p><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T007<br><b>Scenario:</b> Folder dump to cleanup index</p><p><img src="../assets/sample-cleanup-proof.svg" style="width:100%;max-width:760px"></p><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Receipts, screenshots, project photos, notes, links, and mixed folder names.</li><li>Problem: owner cannot find proof, cost notes, or next actions.</li><li>Goal: separate reference, proof, receipts, action items, and archive.</li></ul><h2>Folder map</h2><table><tr><th>Folder</th><th>What goes there</th><th>Rule</th></tr><tr><td>01 Receipts</td><td>Purchases, order confirmations, paid invoices.</td><td>Use date_vendor_amount.</td></tr><tr><td>02 Proof Photos</td><td>Before, during, after, damage, progress.</td><td>Keep original photos.</td></tr><tr><td>03 Reference</td><td>Links, product ideas, sketches, notes.</td><td>Not proof, not action.</td></tr><tr><td>04 Action Needed</td><td>Anything requiring reply, purchase, decision.</td><td>Every item needs owner action.</td></tr><tr><td>99 Archive</td><td>Old or inactive files.</td><td>Do not delete unless confirmed.</td></tr></table><h2>Customer-ready summary</h2><div class="note">Your files are not useless; they are mixed. The first win is to sort proof from action so the next reply, purchase, or decision is visible.</div></body></html>